:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt">The impact of SARs is debated: </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt">House of Lords European Union Committee, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">Money Laundering and the Financing of Terrorism</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt"> HL 132 (2008–09) and HL 11 (2010-11).</span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><a name="_ftn6"></a><a href="#_ftnref6">[6]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt">Terrorism Act 2000, Sch 3A, as substituted by: Terrorism Act 2000 (Business in the Regulated Sector and Supervisory Authorities) Order 2007, SI 2007/3288; Terrorism Act 2000 and Proceeds of Crime Act 2002 (Amendment) Regulations 2007, SI 2007/3398. </span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn7"></a><a href="#_ftnref7">[7]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt">Home Office, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">Regulatory Impact Assessment: Terrorist Property</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt"> (</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt">London: </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt">2001) para 8.</span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><a name="_ftn8"></a><a href="#_ftnref8">[8]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New 